532  vipldws2_B.o[0U] = 0;



533  vipldws2_B.o[1U] = 1;



534  vipldws2_B.o[2U] = 2;



535  vipldws2_B.o[3U] = 3;



536  vipldws2_B.o[4U] = 4;



537  isEnd = false;



538  vipldws2_B.c[1U] = 0;



539



540  /* if hDims < uDims then the all INSIDE sector will not be pushed into the boundary sectors... hence the counter needs to skip the all INSIDEs sector and start from one sector down. */



541  vipldws2_B.c[0U] = 1;



542  while (!isEnd) {



543    uOrigin = 0;



544    yPost = 0;



545



546    /* compute on-boundary sector */



547    /* compute sector if not empty */



548    if (!((vipldws2_B.mWidth[vipldws2_B.o[vipldws2_B.c[0U]] << 1] <= 0) ||



549          (vipldws2_B.mWidth[(vipldws2_B.o[vipldws2_B.c[1U]] << 1) + 1] <= 0)))



550    {



551      /* compute sector for this dim */



552      /* sector start corresponds to margin loc */



553      /* apply offset of margin width for sector end */



554      /* Inside Sector if 0 in all dimensions */



555      isSEmpty = (vipldws2_B.o[vipldws2_B.c[0]] == 0);



556      dimIsPre = ((vipldws2_B.o[vipldws2_B.c[0]] == 3) ||



557                  (vipldws2_B.o[vipldws2_B.c[0]] == 1));



558      if (dimIsPre || isSEmpty) {



559        vipldws2_B.sPreEdges[0] = 0;



560        uOrigin = 1;



561      }



562



563      if ((!(dimIsPre || isSEmpty)) || isSEmpty) {



564        vipldws2_B.sPostEdges[0] = 0;



565        yPost = 1;



566      }



567



568      /* compute sector for this dim */



569      /* sector start corresponds to margin loc */



570      /* apply offset of margin width for sector end */



571      /* Inside Sector if 0 in all dimensions */



572      isSEmpty = (vipldws2_B.o[vipldws2_B.c[1]] == 0);



573      dimIsPre = ((vipldws2_B.o[vipldws2_B.c[1]] == 3) ||



574                  (vipldws2_B.o[vipldws2_B.c[1]] == 1));



575      if (dimIsPre || isSEmpty) {



576        vipldws2_B.sPreEdges[uOrigin] = 1;



577        uOrigin++;



578      }



579



580      if ((!(dimIsPre || isSEmpty)) || isSEmpty) {



581        vipldws2_B.sPostEdges[yPost] = 1;



582        yPost++;



583      }



584



585      /* setup indices for the loops */



586      /* Origin stores the origin of Y with respect to U */



587      /*  where the origin of Y is at its top left corner */



588      /* Compute offset between origin of Y and origin of U(0,0) */



589      vipldws2_B.offset[0U] = -yOrigin[0U];



590      vipldws2_B.offset[1U] = -yOrigin[1U];



591



592      /* sector start and end were computed relative to U */



593      /* make them relative to Y by adding offset */



594      vipldws2_B.sStart[0U] = vipldws2_B.mLoc[vipldws2_B.o[vipldws2_B.c[0]] << 1]



595        + vipldws2_B.offset[0U];



596      vipldws2_B.sEnd[0U] = ((vipldws2_B.mLoc[vipldws2_B.o[vipldws2_B.c[0]] << 1]



597        + vipldws2_B.mWidth[vipldws2_B.o[vipldws2_B.c[0]] << 1]) +



598        vipldws2_B.offset[0U]) - 1;



599      vipldws2_B.sStart[1U] = vipldws2_B.mLoc[(vipldws2_B.o[vipldws2_B.c[1]] <<



600        1) + 1] + vipldws2_B.offset[1U];



601      vipldws2_B.sEnd[1U] = ((vipldws2_B.mLoc[(vipldws2_B.o[vipldws2_B.c[1]] <<



602        1) + 1] + vipldws2_B.mWidth[(vipldws2_B.o[vipldws2_B.c[1]] << 1) + 1]) +



603        vipldws2_B.offset[1U]) - 1;



604



605      /* adjust offset for kernel center */



606      vipldws2_B.offset[0U] -= hLoc[0U];



607      vipldws2_B.offset[1U] -= hLoc[1U];



608



609      /* loop kernel over data */



610      vipldws2_B.idxB[1U] = vipldws2_B.sStart[1U];



611      while (vipldws2_B.idxB[1U] <= vipldws2_B.sEnd[1U]) {



612        vipldws2_B.idxA[1U] = vipldws2_B.idxB[1U] - vipldws2_B.offset[1U];



613        vipldws2_B.idxBLin_c[1U] = yDims[0U] * vipldws2_B.idxB[1U];



614        vipldws2_B.idxB[0U] = vipldws2_B.sStart[0U];



615        while (vipldws2_B.idxB[0U] <= vipldws2_B.sEnd[0U]) {



616          vipldws2_B.idxA[0U] = vipldws2_B.idxB[0U] - vipldws2_B.offset[0U];



617          vipldws2_B.idxBLin_c[0U] = vipldws2_B.idxBLin_c[1U] + vipldws2_B.idxB



618            [0U];



619



620          /* loop over kernel and compute conv/corr */



621          hPost = 0;



622          acc = 0.0F;



623



624          /* loop over kernel */



625          vipldws2_B.hIdxA_k[1U] = 0;



626          while (vipldws2_B.hIdxA_k[1U] <= vipldws2_B.hEnd[1U]) {



627            vipldws2_B.hIdxB[1U] = vipldws2_B.idxA[1U] + vipldws2_B.hIdxA_k[1U];



628            vipldws2_B.hIdxA_k[0U] = 0;



629            while (vipldws2_B.hIdxA_k[0U] <= vipldws2_B.hEnd[0U]) {



630              vipldws2_B.hIdxB[0U] = vipldws2_B.idxA[0U] + vipldws2_B.hIdxA_k[0U];



631              uI = PadBRepl_uS(&u[0U], &vipldws2_B.uStride[0U],



632                               &vipldws2_B.hIdxB[0U], &vipldws2_B.uOrigin[0U],



633                               &vipldws2_B.uEnd[0U], uOrigin,



634                               &vipldws2_B.sPreEdges[0U], yPost,



635                               &vipldws2_B.sPostEdges[0U]);



636              acc += uI * h[hPost];



637              hPost++;



638              vipldws2_B.hIdxA_k[0U]++;



639            }



640



641            vipldws2_B.hIdxA_k[1U]++;



642          }



643



644          if (vipldws2_B.idxBLin_c[0U] >= 0) {



645            y[vipldws2_B.idxBLin_c[0U]] = acc;



646          }



647



648          vipldws2_B.idxB[0U]++;



649        }



650



651        vipldws2_B.idxB[1U]++;



652      }



653    }



654



655    /* advance sector counter */



656    uOrigin = 0;



657    while (uOrigin < 2) {



658      vipldws2_B.c[uOrigin]++;



659      if (vipldws2_B.c[uOrigin] <= 2) {



660        isEnd = false;



661        uOrigin = 2;



662      } else {



663        vipldws2_B.c[uOrigin] = 0;



664        isEnd = true;



665      }



666



667      uOrigin++;



668    }



669  }



670



671  /* End of S-Function (svip2dfirfilter): '<S3>/2-D FIR Filter' */



672}



673



674real32_T rt_roundf_snf(real32_T u)



675{



676  real32_T y;



677  if ((real32_T)fabs(u) < 8.388608E+6F) {



678    if (u >= 0.5F) {



679      y = (real32_T)floor(u + 0.5F);



680    } else if (u > -0.5F) {



681      y = u * 0.0F;



682    } else {



683      y = (real32_T)ceil(u - 0.5F);



684    }



685  } else {



686    y = u;



687  }



688



689  return y;



690}



691



692void LDLf_int32_Treal32_T(real32_T out[], real32_T vArray[], int32_T nRows,



693  const real32_T in[])



694{



695  int32_T c;



696  int32_T r;



697  int32_T idx1;



698  int32_T idx2;



699  real32_T mYTmp;



700  real32_T mYTmpR;



701  boolean_T done;



702  int32_T k;



703



704  /* S-Function (sdspldl2): '<S48>/LDL Factorization' */



705  done = false;



706



707  /* use done to control the for loop return early  */



708  /* when non-positive definite eigenvalue is detected */



709  c = 0;



710  while ((c < nRows) && (!done)) {



711    idx2 = c * nRows;



712    for (r = 0; r < c; r++) {



713      idx1 = r * nRows;



714      vArray[r] = out[idx1 + c] * out[idx1 + r];



715    }



716



717    mYTmp = in[idx2 + c];



718    idx1 = c;



719    for (r = 0; r < c; r++) {



720      mYTmp -= out[idx1] * vArray[r];



721      idx1 += nRows;



722    }



723



724    mYTmpR = mYTmp;



725    if (mYTmp <= 0.0F) {



726      done = true;



727    } else {



728      out[idx2 + c] = mYTmp;



729      for (r = c + 1; r < nRows; r++) {



730        mYTmp = in[idx2 + r];



731        idx1 = r;



732        for (k = 0; k < c; k++) {



733          mYTmp -= out[idx1] * vArray[k];



734          idx1 += nRows;



735        }



736



737        out[idx2 + r] = mYTmp / mYTmpR;



738      }



739    }



740



741    c++;



742  }



743



744  /* transpose and copy lower sub-triang to upper */



745  c = 0;



746  while ((c < nRows) && (!done)) {



747    for (r = c + 1; r < nRows; r++) {



748      out[r * nRows + c] = out[c * nRows + r];



749    }



750



751    c++;



752  }



753



754  /* End of S-Function (sdspldl2): '<S48>/LDL Factorization' */



755}



756



757/* Model step function */



758void vipldws2_step(void)



759{



760  uint8_T tmp;



761  boolean_T c_gotAlLeastOneYellowPixelInThe;



762  boolean_T prevEdgeIsVertical;



763  int8_T idxTmpArray[2];



764  boolean_T countTwice;



765  int8_T idxTmpArray_0[2];



766  boolean_T done;



767  static const int8_T tmp_0[4] = { 1, 0, 3, 2 };



768



769  static const int8_T tmp_1[12] = { 1, 0, 3, 2, 5, 4, 7, 6, 9, 8, 11, 10 };



770



771  int8_T lineColorIdx_idx_0;



772  int8_T solidBrokenIdx_idx_0;



773  int32_T exitg1;



774



775  /* Reset subsysRan breadcrumbs */



776  srClearBC(vipldws2_DW.SampleandHold_SubsysRanBC);



777



778  /* Reset subsysRan breadcrumbs */



779  srClearBC(vipldws2_DW.Enablesignalgenerator_SubsysRan);



780



781  /* Reset subsysRan breadcrumbs */



782  srClearBC(vipldws2_DW.Core_SubsysRanBC);



783



784  /* Reset subsysRan breadcrumbs */



785  srClearBC(vipldws2_DW.Options_SubsysRanBC);



786



787  /* Reset subsysRan breadcrumbs */



788  srClearBC(vipldws2_DW.Differencebetweentwolines_Subsy);



789



790  /* Reset subsysRan breadcrumbs */



791  srClearBC(vipldws2_DW.Selectalinefromtherepositoryifi);



792



793  /* Reset subsysRan breadcrumbs */



794  srClearBC(vipldws2_DW.Draw3rdLine_SubsysRanBC);



795



796  /* Reset subsysRan breadcrumbs */



797  srClearBC(vipldws2_DW.DrawPolygon_SubsysRanBC);



798



799  /* Reset subsysRan breadcrumbs */



800  srClearBC(vipldws2_DW.Subsystem_SubsysRanBC);



801



802  /* S-Function (v4l2_video_capture_sfcn): '<S2>/V4L2 Video Capture' */



803  MW_videoCaptureOutput(vipldws2_ConstP.V4L2VideoCapture_p1,



804                        &vipldws2_B.MatrixConcatenate[0],



805                        &vipldws2_B.MatrixConcatenate[76800],



806                        &vipldws2_B.MatrixConcatenate[153600]);



807



808  /* S-Function (sviprotate): '<S2>/Rotate' */



809  vipldws2_B.indxI = 0;



810  vipldws2_B.planeOffset = 239;



811  for (vipldws2_B.plane = 0; vipldws2_B.plane < 3; vipldws2_B.plane++) {



812    for (vipldws2_B.i = 0; vipldws2_B.i < 240; vipldws2_B.i++) {



813      vipldws2_B.C2 = vipldws2_B.planeOffset - vipldws2_B.i;



814      for (vipldws2_B.j = 0; vipldws2_B.j < 320; vipldws2_B.j++) {



815        vipldws2_B.Rotate[vipldws2_B.C2] =



816          vipldws2_B.MatrixConcatenate[vipldws2_B.indxI];



817        vipldws2_B.indxI++;



818        vipldws2_B.C2 += 240;



819      }



820    }



821



822    vipldws2_B.planeOffset += 76800;



823  }



824



825  /* End of S-Function (sviprotate): '<S2>/Rotate' */



826



827  /* MATLAB Function: '<S2>/MATLAB Function1' */



828  /* MATLAB Function 'Input/MATLAB Function1': '<S26>:1' */



829  /* '<S26>:1:3' y = flip(u,2); */



830  memcpy(&vipldws2_B.y_g[0], &vipldws2_B.Rotate[0], 230400U * sizeof(uint8_T));



831  for (vipldws2_B.j = 0; vipldws2_B.j < 3; vipldws2_B.j++) {



832    for (vipldws2_B.i = 0; vipldws2_B.i < 240; vipldws2_B.i++) {



833      vipldws2_B.planeWidth = vipldws2_B.j * 76800 + vipldws2_B.i;



834      for (vipldws2_B.indxI = 0; vipldws2_B.indxI < 160; vipldws2_B.indxI++) {



835        tmp = vipldws2_B.y_g[vipldws2_B.indxI * 240 + vipldws2_B.planeWidth];



836        vipldws2_B.y_g[vipldws2_B.planeWidth + vipldws2_B.indxI * 240] =



837          vipldws2_B.y_g[(319 - vipldws2_B.indxI) * 240 + vipldws2_B.planeWidth];



838        vipldws2_B.y_g[vipldws2_B.planeWidth + (319 - vipldws2_B.indxI) * 240] =



839          tmp;



840      }



841    }



842  }



843



844  /* End of MATLAB Function: '<S2>/MATLAB Function1' */



845



846  /* S-Function (svipscalenconvert): '<S2>/Image Data Type Conversion' */



847  for (vipldws2_B.i = 0; vipldws2_B.i < 230400; vipldws2_B.i++) {



848    vipldws2_B.ImageDataTypeConversion[vipldws2_B.i] = (real32_T)



849      vipldws2_B.y_g[vipldws2_B.i] / 255.0F;



850  }



851



852  /* End of S-Function (svipscalenconvert): '<S2>/Image Data Type Conversion' */



853



854  /* S-Function (svipcolorconv): '<S2>/Color Space  Conversion' */



855  for (vipldws2_B.i = 0; vipldws2_B.i < 76800; vipldws2_B.i++) {



856    vipldws2_B.ColorSpaceConversion[vipldws2_B.i] =



857      (vipldws2_B.ImageDataTypeConversion[76800 + vipldws2_B.i] * 0.587F +



858       vipldws2_B.ImageDataTypeConversion[vipldws2_B.i] * 0.299F) +



859      vipldws2_B.ImageDataTypeConversion[153600 + vipldws2_B.i] * 0.114F;



860    if (vipldws2_B.ColorSpaceConversion[vipldws2_B.i] > 1.0F) {



861      vipldws2_B.ColorSpaceConversion[vipldws2_B.i] = 1.0F;



862    } else {



863      if (vipldws2_B.ColorSpaceConversion[vipldws2_B.i] < 0.0F) {



864        vipldws2_B.ColorSpaceConversion[vipldws2_B.i] = 0.0F;



865      }



866    }



867  }



868



869  /* End of S-Function (svipcolorconv): '<S2>/Color Space  Conversion' */



870



871  /* S-Function (sdspsubmtrx): '<S2>/Clip image' */



872  vipldws2_B.indxI = 0;



873  for (vipldws2_B.i = 0; vipldws2_B.i < 320; vipldws2_B.i++) {



874    memcpy(&vipldws2_B.Clipimage[vipldws2_B.indxI],



875           &vipldws2_B.ColorSpaceConversion[vipldws2_B.i * 240 + 120], 120U *



876           sizeof(real32_T));



877    vipldws2_B.indxI += 120;



878  }



879



880  /* End of S-Function (sdspsubmtrx): '<S2>/Clip image' */



881



882  /* S-Function (svip2dfirfilter): '<S3>/2-D FIR Filter' */



883  /* Dimensions of the filter */



884  vipldws2_B.h1Dims[0U] = 1;



885  vipldws2_B.h1Dims[1U] = 3;



886  vipldws2_B.uDims[0U] = 120;



887  vipldws2_B.uDims[1U] = 320;



888



889  /* set up kernel related coordinates */



890  /* compute center */



891  /* hLoc is the location of top left corner relative to the center of kernel. */



892  vipldws2_B.hLoc[0U] = 0;



893



894  /* compute center */



895  /* hLoc is the location of top left corner relative to the center of kernel. */



896  vipldws2_B.hLoc[1U] = -1;



897



898  /* Region of Support (ROS) definition: A selected region that restricts the input space for processing. */



899  /* ====================================================== */



900  /*                       ---------------------            */



901  /*                      |ROI                  |           */



902  /*                      |                     |           */



903  /*  ----------------------------------------------------  */



904  /* | INPUT(u)           |                     |         | */



905  /* |                    |                     |         | */



906  /* |   ---------------------------------------------    | */



907  /* |  | ROS             |OUTPUT(y)////////////|     |   | */



908  /* |  |                 |/////////////////////|     |   | */



909  /* |  |                  ---------------------      |   | */



910  /* |  |                                             |   | */



911  /* The user's output mode choices of 'Valid', 'Same as input' and 'Full' map onto correspending definitions of a rectangular ROS. */



912  /* Output range support is computed as an intersection of ROS with Region of Interest (ROI) */



913  /* ///////////////////// */



914  /* begin ROS computation */



915  /* compute ROS based on u, h and output mode */



916  /* ROS is SAME AS INPUT */



917  /* end ROS computation */



918  /* /////////////////// */



919  /* ///////////////////////// */



920  /* begin y sizes computation */



921  /* we need to compute yOrigin and yEnd */



922  /* yOrigin definition: Location of center of reference (origin) of output (y) coordintate system with respect to input (u) coordinate system */



923  /* y sizes are same as ros sizes because there is no ROI */



924  vipldws2_B.yOrigin[0U] = 0;



925  vipldws2_B.yDims[0U] = 120;



926



927  /* y sizes are same as ros sizes because there is no ROI */



928  vipldws2_B.yOrigin[1U] = 0;



929  vipldws2_B.yDims[1U] = 320;



930



931  /* make yOrigin same as roiLoc when y is empty */



932  /* end y sizes computation */



933  /* /////////////////////// */



934  vipldws2_Corr_M_IBRepl_uS_hS_yS(&vipldws2_P.uDFIRFilter_filterMtrx[0U],



935    &vipldws2_B.hLoc[0U], &vipldws2_B.h1Dims[0U], &vipldws2_B.Clipimage[0U],



936    &vipldws2_B.uDims[0U], &vipldws2_B.uDFIRFilter[0U], &vipldws2_B.yDims[0U],



937    &vipldws2_B.yOrigin[0U]);



938



939  /* Saturate: '<S3>/Saturation' */



940  /* check if any input is empty



941   */



942  for (vipldws2_B.i = 0; vipldws2_B.i < 38400; vipldws2_B.i++) {



943    if (vipldws2_B.uDFIRFilter[vipldws2_B.i] > vipldws2_P.Saturation_UpperSat) {



944      vipldws2_B.Saturation[vipldws2_B.i] = vipldws2_P.Saturation_UpperSat;



945    } else if (vipldws2_B.uDFIRFilter[vipldws2_B.i] <



946               vipldws2_P.Saturation_LowerSat) {



947      vipldws2_B.Saturation[vipldws2_B.i] = vipldws2_P.Saturation_LowerSat;



948    } else {



949      vipldws2_B.Saturation[vipldws2_B.i] = vipldws2_B.uDFIRFilter[vipldws2_B.i];



950    }



951  }



952



953  /* End of Saturate: '<S3>/Saturation' */



954



955  /* S-Function (svipgraythresh): '<S3>/Image thresholding' */



956  for (vipldws2_B.i = 0; vipldws2_B.i < 256; vipldws2_B.i++) {



957    vipldws2_DW.Imagethresholding_P_DW[vipldws2_B.i] = 0.0F;



958    vipldws2_DW.Imagethresholding_MU_DW[vipldws2_B.i] = 0.0F;



959  }



960



961  vipldws2_B.scale = 255.0F;



962  for (vipldws2_B.i = 0; vipldws2_B.i < 38400; vipldws2_B.i++) {



963    if (vipldws2_B.Saturation[vipldws2_B.i] < 0.0F) {



964      vipldws2_DW.Imagethresholding_P_DW[0]++;



965    } else if (vipldws2_B.Saturation[vipldws2_B.i] > 1.0F) {



966      vipldws2_DW.Imagethresholding_P_DW[255]++;



967    } else {



968      vipldws2_DW.Imagethresholding_P_DW[(uint8_T)



969        (vipldws2_B.Saturation[vipldws2_B.i] * vipldws2_B.scale + 0.5F)]++;



970    }



971  }



972



973  for (vipldws2_B.i = 0; vipldws2_B.i < 256; vipldws2_B.i++) {



974    vipldws2_DW.Imagethresholding_P_DW[vipldws2_B.i] /= 38400.0F;



975  }



976



977  vipldws2_DW.Imagethresholding_MU_DW[0] = vipldws2_DW.Imagethresholding_P_DW[0];



978  vipldws2_B.cnt = 2.0F;



979  for (vipldws2_B.i = 0; vipldws2_B.i < 255; vipldws2_B.i++) {



980    vipldws2_DW.Imagethresholding_MU_DW[vipldws2_B.i + 1] =



981      vipldws2_DW.Imagethresholding_P_DW[vipldws2_B.i + 1] * vipldws2_B.cnt +



982      vipldws2_DW.Imagethresholding_MU_DW[vipldws2_B.i];



983    vipldws2_B.cnt++;

10397        - 1) << 1) + 1];



10398      vipldws2_B.Switch1[1] = vipldws2_B.Selector1[1];



10399    } else {



10400      /* Selector: '<S39>/Selector2' */



10401      vipldws2_B.Selector2[0] = vipldws2_B.Assignment_i[(vipldws2_B.ForIterator



10402        - 1) << 1];



10403      vipldws2_B.Switch1[0] = vipldws2_B.Selector2[0];



10404



10405      /* Selector: '<S39>/Selector2' */



10406      vipldws2_B.Selector2[1] = vipldws2_B.Assignment_i[((vipldws2_B.ForIterator



10407        - 1) << 1) + 1];



10408      vipldws2_B.Switch1[1] = vipldws2_B.Selector2[1];



10409    }



10410



10411    /* End of Switch: '<S39>/Switch1' */



10412



10413    /* Assignment: '<S39>/Assignment' */



10414    vipldws2_B.Assignment[(vipldws2_B.ForIterator - 1) << 1] =



10415      vipldws2_B.Switch1[0];



10416    vipldws2_B.Assignment[1 + ((vipldws2_B.ForIterator - 1) << 1)] =



10417      vipldws2_B.Switch1[1];



10418    vipldws2_B.s39_iter++;



10419  }



10420



10421  /* End of Outputs for SubSystem: '<S4>/Update' */



10422



10423  /* Update for UnitDelay: '<S38>/FixPt Unit Delay2' incorporates:



10424   *  Constant: '<S38>/FixPt Constant'



10425   */



10426  vipldws2_DW.FixPtUnitDelay2_DSTATE = vipldws2_P.FixPtConstant_Value_e;



10427  for (vipldws2_B.i = 0; vipldws2_B.i < 40; vipldws2_B.i++) {



10428    /* Switch: '<S38>/Reset' incorporates:



10429     *  Constant: '<S2>/Constant'



10430     *  Constant: '<S38>/Initial Condition'



10431     */



10432    if (vipldws2_P.Constant_Value_g) {



10433      vipldws2_B.Xnew[vipldws2_B.i] =



10434        vipldws2_P.UnitDelayResettable1_vinit[vipldws2_B.i];



10435    } else {



10436      vipldws2_B.Xnew[vipldws2_B.i] = vipldws2_B.Assignment[vipldws2_B.i];



10437    }

10439    /* End of Switch: '<S38>/Reset' */



10440



10441    /* Update for UnitDelay: '<S38>/FixPt Unit Delay1' */



10442    vipldws2_DW.FixPtUnitDelay1_DSTATE[vipldws2_B.i] =



10443      vipldws2_B.Xnew[vipldws2_B.i];



10444  }

10447   *  Constant: '<S37>/FixPt Constant'



10448   */

10450

10452  memcpy(&vipldws2_DW.FixPtUnitDelay1_DSTATE_d[0], &vipldws2_B.Xnew_m[0], 20U *



10453         sizeof(int32_T));

10468  vipldws2_DW.Delay_DSTATE = vipldws2_B.outMsg;



10469



10470  /* Update for Delay: '<S17>/Delay1' */



10471  vipldws2_DW.Delay1_DSTATE_e = vipldws2_B.RawMessage;



10472



10473  /* External mode */



10474  rtExtModeUploadCheckTrigger(1);



10475



10476  {                                    /* Sample time: [0.033333333333333333s, 0.0s] */



10477    rtExtModeUpload(0, vipldws2_M->Timing.taskTime0);



10478  }



10479



10480  /* signal main to stop simulation */



10481  {                                    /* Sample time: [0.033333333333333333s, 0.0s] */



10482    if ((rtmGetTFinal(vipldws2_M)!=-1) &&



10483        !((rtmGetTFinal(vipldws2_M)-vipldws2_M->Timing.taskTime0) >



10484          vipldws2_M->Timing.taskTime0 * (DBL_EPSILON))) {



10485      rtmSetErrorStatus(vipldws2_M, "Simulation finished");



10486    }



10487



10488    if (rtmGetStopRequested(vipldws2_M)) {



10489      rtmSetErrorStatus(vipldws2_M, "Simulation finished");



10490    }



10491  }



10492



10493  /* Update absolute time for base rate */



10494  /* The "clockTick0" counts the number of times the code of this task has



10495   * been executed. The absolute time is the multiplication of "clockTick0"



10496   * and "Timing.stepSize0". Size of "clockTick0" ensures timer will not



10497   * overflow during the application lifespan selected.



10498   */



10499  vipldws2_M->Timing.taskTime0 =



10500    (++vipldws2_M->Timing.clockTick0) * vipldws2_M->Timing.stepSize0;



10501}
